Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.63,0:00:24.29,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Oceanus...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.19,0:00:45.52,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Here we are, just strolling into town.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.52,0:00:47.27,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Why the change of heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.73,0:00:48.88,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,No reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.88,0:00:50.47,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I just felt like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.90,0:00:55.20,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, you keep talking about\Ngoing out and seeing the sights.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.64,0:00:59.46,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Exploring the exotic markets \Nof a foreign land
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.46,0:01:02.54,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,is just as exciting as fighting a war on its soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.05,0:01:06.15,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I find it rather pathetic for one \Ncountry to invade another
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.15,0:01:07.79,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,for a reason like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.08,0:01:09.40,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,What's that, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.40,0:01:12.40,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,You speak as though you've \Nexperienced it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.55,0:01:14.67,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.67,0:01:15.90,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing for you to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.86,0:02:57.69,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.71,0:03:01.16,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,This is too cruel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.66,0:03:06.06,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,We devoted ourselves to this masterpiece...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.06,0:03:07.19,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,They've gone too far!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.63,0:03:08.63,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,How...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.63,0:03:12.58,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,How can they call themselves human?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.94,0:03:19.75,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Ryuunosuke...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.75,0:03:22.92,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Only a very select few are capable
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.92,0:03:26.23,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,of understanding true beauty and harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.23,0:03:29.68,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,To the vulgar masses, the philistines,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.68,0:03:32.77,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,such beauty is but a target for destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.65,0:03:40.03,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we had too much fun with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.28,0:03:43.66,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,And now, we're being punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.80,0:03:48.16,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Heed my words, Ryuunosuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.99,0:03:51.33,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,God does not punish humans!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.33,0:03:53.17,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,He merely toys with their lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.60,0:03:55.17,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.60,0:03:59.46,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Once, I committed atrocities so numerous
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.46,0:04:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I was like an embodiment \Nof blasphemy in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.83,0:04:05.72,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,But no matter how many \NI killed or maimed,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.72,0:04:08.04,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,my punishment never came!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.49,0:04:09.90,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,And when I finally paused,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.90,0:04:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I realized my pursuit of the \Nmost heinous cruelties
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.14,0:04:15.16,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,had gone uninterrupted for eight years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.16,0:04:19.61,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, it was not God \Nwho brought ruin unto me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.61,0:04:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the selfishness of my fellow man!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.06,0:04:27.62,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,The Church and monarchy \Nconvicted and executed me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.62,0:04:30.15,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,under the pretense of justice, \Nso they could rob me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.15,0:04:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of my wealth and my land!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.14,0:04:36.59,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,My rampage was halted not \Nby divine judgment.  Far from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.59,0:04:39.21,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,It was simple thievery!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:43.18,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,But, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.72,0:04:47.53,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,God still exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.80,0:04:55.19,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you, a faithless man who knows \Nnothing of miracles, say such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.19,0:04:58.91,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,Because, on the surface, \Nthis world looks bland and boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.91,0:05:03.19,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,But the more you look, the more\Nfun and surprising things you find!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.52,0:05:05.42,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I've always felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.42,0:05:08.89,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,This world, full of strange \Nand wonderful things,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.89,0:05:11.63,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,could not have happened by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.63,0:05:14.10,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,All you need to do is resolve to enjoy it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.10,0:05:17.46,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,and this world is the \Nfinest entertainment!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.87,0:05:21.24,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,You can't have a story \Nof five billion characters
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.24,0:05:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,without an entertainer for an author.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.79,0:05:27.02,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,And if we're talking about this author,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.02,0:05:30.39,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,God is the only name that fits.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.83,0:05:32.51,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell me, Ryuunosuke,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.51,0:05:36.23,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,do you believe that God loves humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.73,0:05:38.73,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,From the bottom of my heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.11,0:05:40.81,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,This world is filled with God's love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.81,0:05:43.47,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,If God spends his every moment \Nwriting a script of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.47,0:05:46.29,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,it must be a labor of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.29,0:05:49.77,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,I bet he's having a blast!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.77,0:05:53.12,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,God is creating a work of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.98,0:05:58.30,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,He loves mankind's ideals, \Nlike bravery and hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.30,0:06:01.66,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,And, by the same token, he loves despair,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.66,0:06:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,bloodshed, and cries of anguish!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.82,0:06:05.07,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,If he didn't,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.07,0:06:09.23,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,he wouldn't have made the insides \Nof all creatures so vibrant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.23,0:06:13.72,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm sure that this world \Nis filled with God's love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.12,0:06:20.44,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,In this era when mankind shuns faith\N and states become secular,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.44,0:06:26.79,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,I have witnessed the birth \Nof a beautiful, new creed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.79,0:06:29.54,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,You have impressed me, Ryuunosuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.54,0:06:31.12,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,My Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.50,0:06:34.16,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, come on, you're making me blush.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.65,0:06:37.61,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,But according to your beliefs,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.61,0:06:40.75,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,my blasphemies were \Nmere comedy, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.75,0:06:45.76,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,No, a true entertainer embraces \Nthe villain's role
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.76,0:06:48.52,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,and leaves the audience smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.52,0:06:54.51,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that God loves playing wise guy \Nto your unrelenting straight man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.65,0:07:03.02,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, blasphemy and praise
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.02,0:07:07.90,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,are equal forms of worship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.90,0:07:10.53,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Ryuunosuke!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.53,0:07:14.80,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,You are the prophet for a new philosophy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.80,0:07:18.25,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,A God who holds all mankind \Nby the marionettes' strings,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.25,0:07:21.87,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,yet is himself a part of the act!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.87,0:07:23.31,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,I understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.80,0:07:27.13,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,His cruel designs finally come clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.38,0:07:28.61,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.06,0:07:32.52,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Then let us create more despair and terror
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.52,0:07:36.52,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,to dye his gardens in even brighter shades.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.87,0:07:41.53,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,We shall teach our Heavenly author
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.53,0:07:45.90,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,that he is not the only one \Nwho knows how to entertain!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.12,0:07:49.75,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,That means we're gonna do \Nsomething wild again, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.01,0:07:53.03,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,So cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.15,0:08:13.47,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"After his victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.47,0:08:18.96,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the king left the governing and politics \Nof his new territory to the local nobility,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.96,0:08:22.76,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}while he continued leading his army\N on their eastward march."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.56,0:08:25.25,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just like in my dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.28,0:08:28.61,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All he wanted to see was \Nthe ocean at the world's end.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.90,0:08:34.52,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He continued his campaign
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.52,0:08:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to see Oceanus with his own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.19,0:08:43.39,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.39,0:08:44.56,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.32,0:08:49.96,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.33,0:08:55.12,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a shrimp, I keep losing\N track of you amidst these shelves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.12,0:08:56.72,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I've been searching for a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.01,0:09:00.49,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Normal people are shorter \Nthan bookshelves, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.05,0:09:02.98,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,What did you buy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.31,0:09:04.49,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Look...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.86,0:09:09.58,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,The new {\i1}Admirable Grand Strategy{\i0} \Ngame came out today!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.58,0:09:11.42,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the first-run special edition!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.19,0:09:16.32,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,My luck stat must be pretty high!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.75,0:09:18.01,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.01,0:09:22.33,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,You can buy the game by itself, but you \Nstill need to have a console to play it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.76,0:09:24.71,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,All taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.88,0:09:27.28,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.28,0:09:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll play each other when we return.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.28,0:09:31.41,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I bought two controllers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.81,0:09:36.47,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested in playing \Nwith low-brow toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.00,0:09:39.13,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.13,0:09:44.36,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Can you never be a bit more open-minded, \Nevery once in a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.36,0:09:47.60,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Do you never try to find something fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.93,0:09:49.40,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:51.71,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,If I had the time to waste,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.71,0:09:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd spend it searching for Truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.77,0:09:57.67,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,And so, your search has led you to...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.09,0:09:59.24,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,This book?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.64,0:10:05.12,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this is about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.45,0:10:07.62,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,What a funny kid you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.62,0:10:11.10,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,You have the genuine article before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.10,0:10:13.63,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to know something, simply ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.64,0:10:17.78,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.64,0:10:24.27,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,The history books all say \Nyou were extremely short.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.58,0:10:28.27,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,So why did you materialize \Nas a ridiculous giant?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.68,0:10:32.15,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,It states that I was short?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.86,0:10:36.94,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose you cannot trust a book
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.94,0:10:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you do not know its author.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.06,0:10:45.12,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,So it's wrong, but you're not mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.61,0:10:49.00,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,No, I really care not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.47,0:10:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.75,0:10:55.98,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Those of power always try to leave \Ntheir mark on history,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.98,0:10:57.51,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,in any era.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.76,0:11:02.27,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose that having your \Nname recorded in books
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.27,0:11:04.96,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,is a form of immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.53,0:11:07.84,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,But if that means that my name
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.84,0:11:10.00,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,will appear in books for a couple thousand years...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.00,0:11:12.04,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to receive
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.41,0:11:15.77,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,one percent of that time in \Nadded to my lifespan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.15,0:11:20.98,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,So it's true that you died \Nin your early thirties?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.42,0:11:23.99,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that one is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.93,0:11:32.44,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.04,0:11:36.82,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,Show God a straight man routine
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.82,0:11:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that will leave his jaw on the floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.78,0:11:40.73,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.73,0:11:43.61,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,You shan't be disappointed, Ryuunosuke!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.61,0:11:47.43,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,This will be, as you might say, \Nthe coolest thing you'll ever see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.87,0:11:49.35,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.35,0:11:52.69,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.97,0:12:09.24,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,This is gonna rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.36,0:12:24.85,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Why so quiet?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.66,0:12:28.79,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.79,0:12:31.81,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I was just lamenting how boring you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.81,0:12:33.78,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.78,0:12:36.42,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,So you admit you're bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.42,0:12:39.01,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Stop being obstinate, and try \Nthis game with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.01,0:12:40.34,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.87,0:12:45.54,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Claiming the Grail just because I \Nhave such a powerful Servant...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.97,0:12:49.29,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like I could be proud of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.02,0:12:54.71,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I would've been better off \Nsummoning Assassin instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.19,0:12:58.93,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, I think not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.31,0:13:01.55,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,You'd likely be dead by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.55,0:13:03.40,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,That suits me fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.40,0:13:06.90,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I have no qualms about dying\N while fighting my own battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.90,0:13:10.12,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm fighting \Nin the Holy Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.56,0:13:11.52,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,But now...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.91,0:13:15.15,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,What would you have me say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.15,0:13:20.56,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Had you perhaps impressed me \Nwith a more ambitious wish,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.56,0:13:25.49,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I would have been more \Nwilling to obey you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.06,0:13:31.45,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,But if all you want is to be taller...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.69,0:13:33.94,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I never said that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.94,0:13:36.43,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be in such a rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.43,0:13:39.19,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,No one said the Grail War
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.19,0:13:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,must be your life's most important event.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.98,0:13:43.73,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.12,0:13:49.95,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, when you find the path in life \Nin which you can take true pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.95,0:13:55.37,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,you must fight for it, \Nwhether or desire to or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.49,0:14:00.44,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Then you'll have the chance to \Nseek your own battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.00,0:14:03.62,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm not the only one dissatisfied
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.62,0:14:05.57,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,with our contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:09.55,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,You don't like it, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.83,0:14:12.25,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Stuck with me for a Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.76,0:14:15.64,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd made a pact with \Na different Master,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.64,0:14:17.83,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,you could've breezed your way to victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.67,0:14:21.24,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.38,0:14:35.39,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:37.85,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,This is the opponent I'm fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.66,0:14:41.59,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Now draw a picture of us two,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.59,0:14:43.73,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,right next to this enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.39,0:14:47.24,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,And do it to scale, that we \Nmay compare ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.66,0:14:48.86,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.27,0:14:50.81,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.81,0:14:53.30,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to the enemy we're facing,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.30,0:14:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you and I are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.24,0:14:57.42,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,No more than dots!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.42,0:15:00.37,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point in comparing our heights?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.76,0:15:04.62,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,That is what makes this exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.62,0:15:06.13,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,The smallest, the weakest...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.13,0:15:07.84,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.84,0:15:10.48,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I should still wish to go and \Ntake over the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.48,0:15:14.02,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,with nothing more than \Nmy tiny dot of a body!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.02,0:15:20.52,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Within my chest beats the heart \Nof the King of Conquerors!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.18,0:15:25.48,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,So then, you don't care \Nwho your Master is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.45,0:15:31.78,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter to you how weak I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.04,0:15:34.68,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Who said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.39,0:15:39.03,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Your own feeling of inferiority
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.03,0:15:42.17,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,signals a fine military leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.57,0:15:44.64,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Despite your grumbling,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.64,0:15:47.65,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,you recognize how small you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.09,0:15:50.00,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,And even still,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.00,0:15:54.05,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,you choose to ignore it, \Nto claw your way to greatness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.63,0:15:56.75,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a compliment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.75,0:15:57.81,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,It's an insult.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.81,0:16:00.00,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.00,0:16:02.84,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,You are a fool, through and through.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.05,0:16:07.57,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Your desires are beyond your abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.57,0:16:10.29,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,"Glory awaits beyond the horizon."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.60,0:16:12.31,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,In my day,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.31,0:16:14.82,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,that was one of life's basic tenets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.82,0:16:19.08,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you kept charging east, \Nlike a crazed maniac?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.39,0:16:21.20,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.20,0:16:24.02,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to see Oceanus with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:27.71,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, my dream never came true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.59,0:16:31.68,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He cannot see the ocean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.54,0:16:38.21,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Oceanus is still my final destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.69,0:16:40.60,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,A dream that never ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.12,0:16:47.11,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That ocean is the place \NRider keeps in his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.11,0:16:48.56,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.92,0:16:52.58,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Two thousand years later, \Nand still I have the same dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.58,0:16:55.21,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Every bit the fool, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.98,0:16:57.79,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,And so, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.79,0:17:02.37,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,A pact with a fellow idiot seems ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.57,0:17:10.67,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,The river.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.26,0:17:28.38,Default,Iry,0000,0000,0000,,Caster...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.40,0:17:32.96,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,Caster must be performing some \Nkind of incredible spell,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.96,0:17:35.37,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,judging by the extreme use of mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.37,0:17:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can be nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.21,0:17:45.91,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, my holy virgin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.34,0:17:50.34,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,I am thrilled to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.34,0:17:52.57,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,You will not learn, monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.57,0:17:54.21,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,What are you playing at tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.55,0:17:56.84,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies, Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.84,0:17:59.63,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,You are not tonight's guest of honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.06,0:18:03.98,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, if you wish to \Nattend the festivities,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.98,0:18:07.80,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,it would please me to no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.80,0:18:09.95,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,I, Gilles de Rais,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.95,0:18:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have prepared a feast of \Ndeath and decadence,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.31,0:18:16.91,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,where all may eat their fill!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.92,0:18:24.55,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Once more, we set out to \Nraise salvation's banner!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.50,0:18:30.79,Default,Iry,0000,0000,0000,,Caster is being absorbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.17,0:18:34.05,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,You, who have been abandoned, \Ngather once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.41,0:18:36.02,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,I shall lead you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.02,0:18:37.76,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,I shall control you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.11,0:18:40.86,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,We have been degraded and humiliated,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.86,0:18:44.06,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,and God himself will know our fury!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.46,0:18:46.81,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God in Heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.81,0:18:50.77,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,I praise your holy name, \Neven as I denounce it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.41,0:18:52.44,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.14,0:18:55.09,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Insolent God!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.37,0:18:57.54,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,Cruel God!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.92,0:19:01.57,Default,Cast,0000,0000,0000,,We shall drag you down from your throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.32,0:19:11.67,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Greetings, King of Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.67,0:19:13.17,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,King of Conquerors...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.17,0:19:14.96,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Easy, easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.96,0:19:17.10,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call a truce for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.10,0:19:19.70,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,We shall have no chance \Nto fight each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.70,0:19:22.57,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,if we cannot first obliterate that beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.57,0:19:25.30,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I've said as much to the other Servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.70,0:19:27.52,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Lancer has agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.52,0:19:29.31,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be here any moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.15,0:19:33.28,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.28,0:19:35.12,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,We shall fight by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.48,0:19:37.48,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,King of Conquerors, though it \Nwill be a short alliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.48,0:19:38.82,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,for tonight, I pledge my loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.15,0:19:42.16,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Einzbern, do you guys have a plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.16,0:19:47.41,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Lancer said you fought Caster before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.41,0:19:50.46,Default,Iry,0000,0000,0000,,We must defeat him as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.46,0:19:53.64,Default,Iry,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, Caster is providing the mana
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.64,0:19:55.69,Default,Iry,0000,0000,0000,,that creature needs to maintain \Nits form in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.69,0:19:59.77,Default,Iry,0000,0000,0000,,But if it finds its own food source and\N becomes able to sustain itself, all is lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.77,0:20:01.47,Default,Iry,0000,0000,0000,,We must kill Caster before that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.01,0:20:03.64,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.64,0:20:05.74,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,So we must end this before it reaches shore
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.74,0:20:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and starts to feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.84,0:20:13.97,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,But Caster has hidden himself deep \Ninside the creature's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.43,0:20:16.49,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,What is your plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.90,0:20:18.17,Default,Lance,0000,0000,0000,,We force him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.61,0:20:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is our only way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.35,0:20:24.32,Default,Lance,0000,0000,0000,,If we can expose his Noble Phantasm,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.32,0:20:28.24,Default,Lance,0000,0000,0000,,my Gáe Dearg can break \Nthe spell in one strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.56,0:20:30.91,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,Lancer, can you throw that spear through
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.91,0:20:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Caster's Noble Phantasm from this coast?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.96,0:20:37.13,Default,Lance,0000,0000,0000,,If I can see it, that is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.56,0:20:40.60,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,Then Rider and I shall meet it headlong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.60,0:20:42.26,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,How sounds that to you, King of Conquerors?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.69,0:20:44.17,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Fine by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.17,0:20:47.24,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,My chariot can travel anywhere, \Nwith or without a road.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.24,0:20:51.14,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,But how will you attack, while the enemy \Nremains in the river, Saber?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.53,0:20:55.02,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,I have the Lady of the Lake's protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.02,0:20:58.69,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,No water can impede me, \Nno matter its depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.91,0:21:02.11,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,That is rare indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.53,0:21:05.82,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I want you for my army even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.28,0:21:09.04,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,You'll pay for that line later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.04,0:21:13.50,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,But now, we must pull Caster from that monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.61,0:21:15.75,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.75,0:21:19.41,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I shall strike first!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.02,0:21:28.95,Default,Iry,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.12,0:21:47.91,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,This ends now, Caster!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.72,0:21:54.12,Title,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 13: \NThe Forbidden Feast of Madness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.33,0:23:27.73,Default,Ryuu,0000,0000,0000,,Go get them, Sir Bluebeard!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.73,0:23:30.27,Default,Zou,0000,0000,0000,,Such a failure is unprecedented.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.27,0:23:32.64,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,You wish me to draw Ea, \Nmy greatest treasure, here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.64,0:23:33.43,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Saber!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.43,0:23:35.27,Default,Toki,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait, King of Heroes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.27,0:23:36.68,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,What a guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.68,0:23:39.59,Default,Kari,0000,0000,0000,,I'll slaughter you all! \NKill every last one!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.45,0:23:39.92,Title,Kari,0000,0000,0000,,Fate/Zero, 2nd Season: Starting April, 2012
